race.comment: RUJI (4) has changed stables since a battling effort here nearly 2 weeks ago when finishing fifth. He was pressured in front that day, and with all things considered, his effort wasn't bad. He meets a relatively poor field here, and with the blinkers off, can have a say in the finish. STARPELLO (5) is trained locally, so he won't have a problem having his first run on the poly surface. He has shown some ability in his short career thus far, and can take this out. DEALERS CHOICE (3) needed her fresh up run here nearly a fortnight ago over 1200m and steps up to a more suitable middle distance here. At least she has won a race, and on that score alone, she has to be respected. TICKFORD (1) is resuming from a spell in a poor field as a 3-race winner. He might need it, but he is still capable of a top 4 finish here. KEEPITINYOURWALLET (6) is getting fitter and was only 2 lengths from the winner here last time out. Include in all combinations. FROSBIE (2) has some place claims here.
